==English==
===Etymology===
Named after Dr. Robert Keinbock, a [[radiologist]] in Vienna who discovered it in 1910.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Keinbock’s [[disease]]'''

# a [[painful]] [[disease]] of the [[wrist]] that results from [[loss]] of [[circulation]] to the [[lunate]] [[bone]]

